# Cost constraints — [APP_NAME]

What's expensive in this project — and the design reflexes that protect the
budget. Per-unit pricing structures, cost-traps that have already burned us,
and the defaults Claude should reach for when proposing functionality.

This file is read by `rsct_get_knowledge(category="cost-constraints")` and
by `rsct_persona_review` (DevOps + Architect personas). Spec phase
surfaces relevant cost reflexes when a proposed option touches a
cost-sensitive area — so "we should add CloudWatch logs" gets a "you
already pay for Datadog, and CloudWatch retention has a cliff at 14 days"
response before the dev signs off.

**Bias correction:** Without this file, Claude proposes functionally
optimal solutions without weighing operational cost. With this file, it
weighs cost as a constraint alongside correctness and maintainability.

---

## When to capture an entry here

Capture or update when **any** of the following is true:

- A bill surprised us. Capture the cause + the reflex to avoid the surprise
again.
- A measurable optimization landed (we reduced a line item by $X/mo).
Capture the technique so it doesn't get reversed by a future "simplification".
- A new vendor or service onboarded; document its pricing structure
(per-request, per-GB, per-host, per-user, tiered, etc.).
- A scaling event is approaching that will change the cost picture (10×
traffic event, new market launch, dataset growth).
- A design decision was made specifically to control cost ("we batch every
60s instead of streaming because per-event cost would 5× the bill").

## When NOT to capture here

- Vendor identity and lock-in — that's `vendor-relationships.md` (which can
cross-reference here for cost detail).
- Sales/pricing strategy for your **own** product — out of scope; this file
is about **operating cost**.
- Generic frugality ("be careful with resources") — capture only when there
is a measured cost driver and a concrete reflex.
- Detailed financial reports — keep them in finance tools; this file
captures **design-relevant** cost insight only.

