## Entry schema

Each entry follows this exact structure:

```
### CC-NNN — <cost area or resource>
- **What costs:** <unit and scale — e.g., "per S3 PUT request",
  "per Datadog host-month", "per OpenAI 1k input tokens">
- **Current spend tier:** <sub-$100/mo / sub-$1k/mo / sub-$10k/mo / higher>
  (sanitized — never write exact bill numbers)
- **Sensitivity to design choices:** <low | medium | high | critical>
  — i.e., how much can a poor design 10× this line?
- **Cost-traps observed (us or industry):** <concrete patterns that bleed
  money — e.g., "writing one log line per HTTP request to CloudWatch with
  default retention">
- **Default reflex when designing in this area:** <the rule of thumb. Be
  specific — "batch writes at 60s", "cap retention at 14 days",
  "always paginate over 100 items">
- **Threshold for revisit:** <when does the cost picture change enough to
  re-evaluate this entry? — e.g., "if user count > 10k", "if monthly
  spend > $X", "when contract renews YYYY-MM">
- **Related:** <ADRs, vendor entries, incidents tied to cost events>
- **Captured:** <YYYY-MM-DD> by <dev|claude>
```

Numbering: CC-001+ sequential, append-only.

