## Example entry (✅ good — keep this style)

### CC-002 — Datadog hosts and custom metrics
- **What costs:** per Datadog host-month + per 100 custom metrics per host
- **Current spend tier:** sub-$1k/mo (12 production hosts + 4 staging)
- **Sensitivity to design choices:** high — adding 1 host = +$X/mo flat; adding ~150 custom metrics across the fleet pushes us into the next billing tier.
- **Cost-traps observed:**
  - Per-pod metrics in Kubernetes deployments (each replica counted as a host) — bit us in 2024-Q3 when autoscaler briefly hit 28 pods overnight; one bill jumped 2.3×.
  - High-cardinality tags (per-user_id, per-tenant_id) explode the custom-metric count silently.
  - Tracing on staging duplicates trace storage costs without business value.
- **Default reflex when designing in this area:**
  - For new services: stay under 100 custom metrics per host, use `_dist` distributions instead of N gauges where possible.
  - For new metrics: avoid tagging with high-cardinality fields; if a per-tenant view is needed, use logs + log-based metric.
  - Disable APM tracing on staging; rely on the smaller free-tier integration there.
  - When scaling out: count the per-host cost in the rollout doc, not just compute cost.
- **Threshold for revisit:** if monthly spend crosses sub-$10k/mo tier OR if production host count > 20.
- **Related:** [[vendor-relationships]] VR-005 (Datadog adoption rationale), [[incident-log]] INC-014 (autoscaler-induced bill spike), ADR-018 (observability split: Datadog for prod, Sentry-only for staging).
- **Captured:** 2025-10-15 by alice

