## Anti-example (❌ do NOT capture this kind of entry here)

```
### CC-XXX — Cloud is expensive
- Reflex: be careful with cloud.
```

**Why this is wrong:** No measurement, no specific resource, no actionable
reflex. A future planning session reading this gets zero signal — every
proposal touches "cloud", every reader knows cloud isn't free.

If the team has actually been burned by a specific cloud line item — egress
fees from cross-region, NAT gateway costs, idle GPU instances, snapshot
proliferation — capture **that** specifically. The narrower the entry, the
sharper the reflex.

